<subSubSection pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="93.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,546,572]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kontuniemi" authorityYear="1946" box="[678,814,546,572]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thorwaldi">
<emphasis box="[678,814,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. thorwaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex of the 
<taxonomicName box="[994,1164,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stramineipes">
<emphasis box="[994,1164,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. stramineipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[1352,1437,546,572]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vafer">
<emphasis box="[1352,1437,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. vafer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[230,427,582,608]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[445,653,582,608]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" pagination="179 - 197" refId="ref76388" refString="Shinohara, A. (1988 b) Pamphilius stramineipes (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) and its close relatives. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 14, 179 - 197." type="journal article" year="1988">Shinohara (1988b)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[959,1099,582,609]" name="South Korea" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">South Korea</collectingCountry>
based on 
<specimenCount box="[1210,1313,582,609]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="male">two male</specimenCount>
specimens as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1976" box="[182,325,618,644]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planifrons">
<emphasis box="[182,325,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. planifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These 
<specimenCount box="[414,529,618,645]" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
actually belong to the new species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Kramp &amp; Taeger" authorityYear="2022" box="[934,1118,618,644]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belokobylskiji">
<emphasis box="[934,1118,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. belokobylskiji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described above, and 
<collectingCountry name="South Korea" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">South Korea</collectingCountry>
is here excluded from the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1976" box="[707,852,654,680]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planifrons">
<emphasis box="[707,852,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. planifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1976" box="[869,1120,654,680]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planifrons">
<emphasis box="[869,1120,654,680]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Pamphilius planifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most closely allied to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhoae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. rhoae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as discussed under the latter species. In the molecular analyses using COI and NaK sequences (
<figureCitation box="[1329,1431,690,716]" captionStart="FIGURE 149" captionStartId="236.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[169,1416,198,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@236.[163,1425,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="236" captionText="FIGURE 149. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." pageId="93" pageNumber="94">Figs 149</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,196,726,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 161" captionStartId="246.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[177,1403,189,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@246.[171,1417,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="246" captionText="FIGURE 161. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 2." pageId="93" pageNumber="94">161</figureCitation>
), the relationships between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Kramp &amp; Taeger" authorityYear="2022" box="[508,692,726,752]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belokobylskiji">
<emphasis box="[508,692,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. belokobylskiji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1976" box="[705,847,726,752]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planifrons">
<emphasis box="[705,847,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. planifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1988" box="[901,994,726,752]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="93" pageNumber="94" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhoae">
<emphasis box="[901,994,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="93" pageNumber="94">P. rhoae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were poorly resolved.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
